{"_id":"0f3onAjAE3hrCf9A","name":"Lokerimon's Unerring Hunter","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.6thYGJOuOh4E5k77"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/hunting-horn.svg","description":"<h1>Lokerimon's Unerring Hunter</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 5</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 10 minutes</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 249</p><br><p>The caster conjures a magical hunter to kill or capture his quarry. This spell creates either a lesser or greater unerring hunter, whose statistics are as follows:</p>\n<p><strong>Unerring Hunter, Lesser:</strong> Init +3, Atk bite +6 melee (dmg [[/roll 3d10+3]]) or paralyzing touch (Fort DC 12 or duration [[/roll 1d5]] days); AC 17; HD [[/roll 8d8+3]]; MV 40&rsquo;; Act [[/roll 1d20]]; SP half-damage from normal weapons, camouflage, see invisible, SV Fort +5, Ref +3, Will +2; AL N.</p>\n<p><strong>Unerring Hunter, Greater:</strong> Init +5, Atk bite +8 melee (dmg [[/roll 4d10+4]]) or paralyzing touch (Fort DC 15 or duration [[/roll 2d4]] days); AC 21; HD [[/roll 10d8+8]]; MV 50&rsquo;; Act [[/roll 2d20]]; SP half-damage from normal weapons, camouflage, see invisible, SV Fort +7, Ref +5, Will +4; AL N.</p>\n<p>Unerring hunters attack to either kill or capture, never both, and use their paralysis attack to incapacitate quarry to return to their master. Unerring hunters can carry a single man-sized or smaller creature without difficulty. They suffer normal damage from weapons of a +1 enchantment or greater and half-damage from normal weapons. They can occlude their forms with shadows to hide themselves and gain a +10 bonus to avoid detection. They can see invisible creatures. Hunters track their victims through magic;</p>\n<p>mundane means by the prey to hide its trail are never successful. Hunters cannot cross magical barriers but will wait patiently for wards to expire or for prey to leave the protected area. Slaying a hunter causes the spell to end and a new hunter cannot be sent against the target until 1 month has passed.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Lokerimon's Unerring Hunter]{Lokerimon's Unerring Hunter}</p>","results":[{"_id":"E5epUQfSSlh4ySAL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint + misfire; (1-3) corruption; (4) patron taint (or corruption if no patron); (5+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"z0CgekFIjaL2AiOX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"K5FU1HuSxymApeTB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":6,"range":[12,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"sByKkBEU2MiqYakJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster conjures a lesser unerring hunter to locate, capture, or kill his enemies. It can take nearly any twisted form the caster desires so long as it is man-sized or smaller. The caster must have an object belonging to the target in order for the hunter to lock on to its victim. Without such an item, the spell fails. <br /><br />If given the wrong item (an object belonging to someone other than the intended quarry), the hunter carries out its mission on the owner of the item regardless of the caster's wishes. The hunter can track down a single target up to 10 miles away and pursues its prey for up to 24 hours before fading out of existence.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qpHwTb8RGsrkGa8c","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster conjures a lesser unerring hunter to locate, capture, or kill his enemies. It can take nearly any twisted form the caster desires so long as it is man-sized or smaller. The caster must have an object belonging to the target in order for the hunter to lock on to its victim. Without such an item, the spell fails. <br /><br />If given the wrong item (an object belonging to someone other than the intended quarry), the hunter carries out its mission on the owner of the item regardless of the caster's wishes.The lesser hunter can track its target up to 50 miles away or until 48 hours have passed.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"GU6Z1wcQfMS8apH1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster conjures a lesser unerring hunter to locate, capture, or kill his enemies. It can take nearly any twisted form the caster desires so long as it is man-sized or smaller. The caster does not need an object belonging to the target, but without it there is a possibility that the hunter fails to \"find the scent\" of its intended prey. If the caster lacks an object but has seen the target personally, the hunter has a 90% chance of successfully tracking the victim. <br /><br />If the caster has seen an image of the intended target, the hunter has a 75% chance of finding its victim. If the caster has only a verbal description of the intended target, the hunter has just a 50% chance of locating its quarry. A hunter that fails to find the scent of its prey dissipates after an hour and the spell cannot be cast again until 24 hours have passed. The unerring hunter can track its target up to 100 miles away or until 7 days have passed.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[24,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"aojGleXn0Jzuvtgu","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster conjures a lesser unerring hunter to locate, capture, or kill his enemies. It can take nearly any twisted form the caster desires so long as it is man-sized or smaller. The caster does not need an object belonging to the target, but without it there is a possibility that the hunter fails to \"find the scent\" of its intended prey. If the caster lacks an object but has seen the target personally, the hunter has a 90% chance of successfully tracking the victim. <br /><br />If the caster has seen an image of the intended target, the hunter has a 75% chance of finding its victim. If the caster has only a verbal description of the intended target, the hunter has just a 50% chance of locating its quarry. A hunter that fails to find the scent of its prey dissipates after an hour and the spell cannot be cast again until 24 hours have passed. The lesser unerring hunter can track prey up to 250 miles away or until two weeks have passed.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[26,28],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MXjvuxdeinSvI5l2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster conjures a greater unerring hunter to locate, capture, or kill his enemies. It can take nearly any twisted form the caster desires so long as it is man-sized or smaller. It tracks its target up to 500 miles away or until 1 month has passed. It always finds the trail of its target regardless of whether the caster has an object belonging to its victim or not.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[29,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"JkH9zY83XxY17nbt","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can either summon forth a lesser unerring hunter that pursues its target regardless of distance/ time until it is either successful or destroyed, or the caster can set a greater unerring hunter against a foe that is up to 1,000 miles away or for up to 3 month's time. He does not need an object belonging to the target.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Cp2QscbFpcDrQzWC","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can either summon up to three unerring hunters to pursue multiple targets or a single greater hunter that relentlessly tracks its target until successful or destroyed. Multiple lesser unerring hunters can be sent against a single target and all three must be destroyed to prevent the spell from being renewed against the target for one month's time. Regardless of whether multiple lesser hunters or a single greater hunter are summoned, there is no limit to time or distance on the hunt, and an object relating to the target is not required.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[36,37],"drawn":false},{"_id":"GuT9MVPkOPF5oAg1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster conjures up three greater unerring hunters to track down his target. These hunters can track their quarry across any distance and into other planes of existence if necessary. They hunt until successful or destroyed. An object belonging to the target is not required.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":62,"range":[38,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"0qLTiSwn7xKn7wrV","name":"Wizard Sense","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.AgboRRkXXzXWnNsX"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/awareness.svg","description":"<h1>Wizard Sense</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 4</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 60' or more (see below)</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round per caster level</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 245</p><br><p>The caster extends his senses beyond the normal human range to observe distant events or glimpse the truth.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Wizard Sense]{Wizard Sense}</p>","results":[{"_id":"pmBzPGwRicFiRdwE","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint + misfire; (1-2) corruption; (3) patron taint (or corruption if no patron); (4+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"SDxl9fR1hblmIyEc","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Iiz08amlNgKCARUP","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":6,"range":[12,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"UrlKcgNQpe8r4xP5","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can see magical auras, invisible creatures, and pierce illusions of all types to see creatures and objects in their true forms. This mystical sight also reveals secret doors and traps if they are present. The enhanced vision has a limit of 60'.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"CCk1pfab8VY3uq8N","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"As above, but the caster also gains x-ray vision, allowing him to see through up to 30' of stone and 60' of wood or other less-dense material. Lead or gold foils x-ray vision.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PLawKFKvphRwXCKq","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster extends his hearing to detect sound and conversation at a distance. The caster must choose a location either well known to him (his own home, for instance) or within sight of his current position (beyond a closed door, a copse of trees, the roof of a nearby tower, etc.). The caster clearly hears any normal noises occurring within a 60' radius of that designated locale.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[24,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"DyDaIIfm7fzOCd7k","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Similar to the above, but the caster extends his vision to observe whatever is in seeing distance from his designated location. Illumination is a factor, and the caster can only observe an area in a 10' radius from his chosen point if the space is dark. The caster's sight is considered normal for this effect and does not gain the additional spectrums of vision noted above.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[26,28],"drawn":false},{"_id":"yZiqEyEdN72OeyZz","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster creates an invisible eye that he can send out to reconnoiter or spy for him. The eye moves at 30' per round and is incorporeal, so it can pass through solid matter. It \"sees\" up to 10' in darkness and up to 60' in brightly lit conditions. The eye can see magical auras, invisible creatures, and discern illusions. It sees traps if they are present. There is no limit on how far the eye may travel from the caster, but it vanishes when the spell expires regardless of position.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[29,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"uiZ9neGw3N4EXcxu","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can see and hear events occurring at a location up to 10 miles away for each level of experience he possesses. The location need not be familiar to him, but if it is not familiar, he must possess an object from the location he wishes to see (e.g., a leaf from a tree at that place, or a stone from a tower at that location, etc.). He is otherwise free to choose his target. <br /><br />Lead and gold shielding do not protect the site from observation, but certain rare, mystic materials might at the judge's discretion. The caster has normal sight and hearing to a range of 60' from the chosen location and can also see invisible creatures, magic auras, traps, and the truth behind illusions.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MKYZBTKZbBCM3obq","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can see and hear events occurring at a location up to 100 miles away for each level of experience he possesses. The location need not be familiar to him, but if it is not familiar, he must possess an object from the location he wishes to see (e.g., a leaf from a tree at that place, or a stone from a tower at that location, etc.). He is otherwise free to choose his target. <br /><br />Lead and gold shielding do not protect the site from observation, but certain rare, mystic materials might at the judge's discretion. The caster has normal sight and hearing to a range of 60' from the chosen location and can also see invisible creatures, magic auras, traps, and the truth behind illusions.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[36,37],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ArqqlaKXLtNXPTPG","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster witnesses events occurring on other planes of existence, with almost unlimited range. He can spy on the happenings in the Halls of Hell, in the palaces of the gods, in the realm of the dead, or into the cold depths of space to watch alien forms at play. The caster can see invisible or concealed creatures in these places. The judge has the final word on what is observed and where and whether those being watched detect the caster's prying eyes.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":62,"range":[38,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"0ynYWNV6SYfl1WmD","name":"Monster Summoning","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.ZQKYsP1wsP4DYkTv"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/brute.svg","description":"<h1>Monster Summoning</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 20'</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 turn or less</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 184</p><br><p>The caster must spend half the casting time drawing pentacle, then the remaining casting time conjuring monster spirits. At end of the turn, the caster summons forth a monster. He must be familiar with the monster, and it must be native to this plane of existence. The master must have some material remnant of the monster to expend in the spell (e.g., hair, fur, paw, tooth, skull, etc.).</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Monster Summoning]{Monster Summoning}</p>","results":[{"_id":"Un7mW5Cuu8Fhr3yY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint + misfire; (1-3) corruption; (4) patron taint (or corruption if no patron); (5+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9mdbkKB8OkQtdgw4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"F7BRkDsWcuvIl2fQ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ocB35B7caWdkF9Ly","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons one monster of 1 HD or less. The monster remains for up to 1 hour as long as it remains in the pentacle, though it hungers, thirsts, and rests as normal. It obeys the caster's commands within normal bounds; suicidal commands or those contrary to its nature have a 50% chance of releasing the monster from service. <br /><br />If the pentacle is broken or service is otherwise ended, the monster returns from whence it came. Due to the nature of the summoning, the caster cannot directly harm a creature he summons.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"EsKEhq496hmPCnpc","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons two 1 HD monsters or one 2 HD monster. The monsters remain for up to 1 hour as long as they remain in the pentacle, though they hunger, thirst, and rest as normal. They obey the caster's commands within normal bounds; suicidal commands or those contrary to its nature have a 50% chance of releasing a monster from service. <br /><br />If the pentacle is broken or service is otherwise ended, the monsters return from whence they came. Due to the nature of the summoning, the caster cannot directly harm a creature he summons.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[16,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"kDxU2t4KzLs2e0An","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons two 1 HD monsters or one 2 HD monster. The monsters remain for up to 1 hour, though they hunger, thirst, and rest as normal. They obey the caster's commands within normal bounds; suicidal commands or those contrary to its nature have a 50% chance of releasing monster from service. <br /><br />If the pentacle is broken or service is otherwise ended, the monsters return from whence they came. Due to the nature of the summoning, the caster cannot directly harm a creature he summons.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[20,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"eHE49FotxLIZLoyy","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons two monsters of 2 HD or less or one 4 HD monster. The monsters remain for up to 2 hours, though they hunger, thirst, and rest as normal. They obey the caster's commands within normal bounds; suicidal commands or those contrary to its nature have a 25% chance of releasing monster from service. <br /><br />If the pentacle is broken or service is otherwise ended, the monsters return from whence they came. Due to the nature of the summoning, the caster cannot directly harm a creature he summons.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[22,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"VQ0QRycWoE6PO2Z3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"With a reduced casting time of four rounds, the caster summons four 1 HD monsters, two 2 HD monsters, or one 4 HD monster. The monsters remain for up to 2 hours, though they hunger, thirst, and rest as normal. They obey the caster's commands within normal bounds; suicidal commands or those contrary to its nature have a 25% chance of releasing monster from service. <br /><br />If the pentacle is broken or service is otherwise ended, the monsters return from whence they came. Due to the nature of the summoning, the caster cannot directly harm a creature he summons.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[26,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ihcoNjR7I0YwOaFS","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"With a reduced casting time of four rounds, the caster summons eight 1 HD monsters, four 2 HD monsters, two 4 HD monsters, or one 8 HD monster. The monsters remain for up to 4 hours, though they hunger, thirst, and rest as normal. <br /><br />They obey the caster's commands within normal bounds; suicidal commands or those contrary to its nature have a 10% chance of releasing monster from service. If the pentacle is broken or service is otherwise ended, the monsters return from whence they came. Due to the nature of the summoning, the caster cannot directly harm a creature he summons.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"EzxuLZ3DonGIelEG","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"With a reduced casting time of only a single round, the caster summons eight 1 HD monsters, four 2 HD monsters, two 4 HD monsters, or one 8 HD monster. The monsters remain for up to 4 hours, though they hunger, thirst, and rest as normal. <br /><br />They obey the caster's commands within normal bounds; suicidal commands or those contrary to its nature have a 10% chance of releasing monster from service. If the pentacle is broken or service is otherwise ended, the monsters return from whence they came. Due to the nature of the summoning, the caster cannot directly harm a creature he summons.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"E0iqpFuyHo5MdDzn","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"With a reduced casting time of only a single round, the caster summons sixteen 1 HD monsters, eight 2 HD monsters, four 4 HD monsters, two 8 HD monsters, or one 16 HD monster. The monsters remain for up to 24 hours, though they hunger, thirst, and rest as normal. <br /><br />They obey the caster's commands within normal bounds; suicidal commands or those contrary to its nature have a 1% chance of releasing monster from service. If the pentacle is broken or service is otherwise ended, the monsters return from whence they came. Due to the nature of the summoning, the caster cannot directly harm a creature he summons.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":66,"range":[34,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"1FKyxgErjDfNQig5","name":"Haste","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.bZKIhrkAb34jhuQQ"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/upgrade.svg","description":"<h1>Haste</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Caster or 20' radius from caster</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> [[/roll 1d4]] rounds or more</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 2 rounds</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> N/A</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 221</p><br><p>The caster gains quickness of motion. The caster&rsquo;s actions are amplified in speed such that he can move at twice the speed of a normal man &ndash; or faster! At higher levels, this spell also affects some creatures within a 20&rsquo; radius of the caster. However, creatures affected by this spell age at an abnormal rate while under its influence. Additional actions gained are as follows:</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> hastened creatures double their movement speed. In some cases it may be tripled, as noted below.</p>\n<p><strong>Action dice:</strong> hastened creatures gain additional action dice. According to their class, these action dice may be used for attacks, spellcasting, turning, laying on hands, or skill checks. If the character currently has only one action die, the extra action die is the same as that one (usually a d20). If the character has multiple action dice (due to high class level or other factor), the extra action die is equal to the character&rsquo;s lowest action die. For example, if the character&rsquo;s action dice are [[/roll 1d20+1]]d14, he gains an extra [[/roll 1d14]] as a third action die.</p>\n<p>This spell can also be cast to cancel the spell @Compendium[dcc-compendium.spells.BWv9jpzTmPL4gZXQ]{Slow}.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Haste]{Haste}</p>","results":[{"_id":"qXfMFzqt5HdYbUnt","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, an