{"_id":"1qwN0SuUp1w1O9uj","name":"Demon Summoning - True Name","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.VW5KfAngyueFaONM"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/daemon-skull.svg","description":"<h1>Demon Summoning - True Name</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 20'</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 turn</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 206</p><br><p>The caster consults with an extraplanar spirit in order to make inquiries or pass on information. The spirit may be the ghost of a deceased person, a demon residing on another plane, a nature spirit occupying a lake or tree, the caster&rsquo;s own supernatural patron, or even a god.</p>\n<p>This spell is most effective if the caster consults with a spirit he already knows. If the caster consults with his patron (per the patron bond spell) or one of the patron&rsquo;s servants, add +1 to the spell check. If the caster consults with another specific spirit known to him from prior contact, legend, logical deduction (e.g., the</p>\n<p>caster sees a dead body and wishes to find its ghost), or research (e.g., the caster has visited his altar or read of his exploits), there is no modifier. If the caster has no knowledge of the spirit consulted, merely wishes to contact any spirit that will answer, or deliberately contacts a spirit of opposed alignment or interests, subtract -1 from the spell check.</p>\n<p>If the spirit is known to the caster, roll d% to determine its attitude: (01-20) friendly, (21-80) neutral, (81-00) hostile. A friendly or neutral spirit answers honestly to the best of its ability and has a base 50% chance of knowing the answer to any given question appropriate to its area of knowledge, modified by the judge&rsquo;s discretion and the obscurity of the question. When questioning a hostile spirit, roll 