{"_id":"28Xvd6PWigEUcrAh","name":"Demon Summoning - Patron","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.Yv9sjWr3K01IEFdn"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/daemon-skull.svg","description":"<h1>Demon Summoning - Patron</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 20'</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 turn</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 206</p><br><p>The caster consults with an extraplanar spirit in order to make inquiries or pass on information. The spirit may be the ghost of a deceased person, a demon residing on another plane, a nature spirit occupying a lake or tree, the caster&rsquo;s own supernatural patron, or even a god.</p>\n<p>This spell is most effective if the caster consults with a spirit he already knows. If the caster consults with his patron (per the patron bond spell) or one of the patron&rsquo;s servants, add +1 to the spell check. If the caster consults with another specific spirit known to him from prior contact, legend, logical deduction (e.g., the</p>\n<p>caster sees a dead body and wishes to find its ghost), or research (e.g., the caster has visited his altar or read of his exploits), there is no modifier. If the caster has no knowledge of the spirit consulted, merely wishes to contact any spirit that will answer, or deliberately contacts a spirit of opposed alignment or interests, subtract -1 from the spell check.</p>\n<p>If the spirit is known to the caster, roll d% to determine its attitude: (01-20) friendly, (21-80) neutral, (81-00) hostile. A friendly or neutral spirit answers honestly to the best of its ability and has a base 50% chance of knowing the answer to any given question appropriate to its area of knowledge, modified by the judge&rsquo;s discretion and the obscurity of the question. When questioning a hostile spirit, roll d%: it (01-50) provides misleading information; (51-80) refuses to answer; (81-95) attempts to probe the caster&rsquo;s</p>\n<p>mind (Will save vs. DC of [[/roll 4d6]] or take [[/roll 1d4]] temporary Int damage); or (96-100) uses this connection to attempt enter the material plane.</p>\n<p>Note that establishing contact in this manner also enables the spirit to establish reverse contact on future</p>\n<p>occasions (by casting this same spell, if it is able, or other similar abilities). Furthermore, not all spirits are pleased at an interruption from a curious mortal. The ghost of a recently slain creature, for example, is probably quite angry at its death, and there may be consequences for awakening it.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Demon Summoning - Patron]{Demon Summoning - Patron}</p>","results":[{"_id":"cpSov1rUIRCJyLtr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint; (1-4) corruption; (5+) patron taint (or corruption if no patron).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"3paInkj6IM2WxwDf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ZRpwgMdTK4JQvCCD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[12,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"zWu9rWDiA6F1XDuX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons a type I demon in service to his patron that remains for [[/roll 1d4+1]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"g3QsitrGgGW3m3PZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons a type I demon in service to his patron that remains for [[/roll 1d4+1]] turns.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[18,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qtAm5HqGdEHdOD28","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons a type II demon in service to his patron that remains for [[/roll 1d4+1]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[22,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"BFJNMjkM7I4jsM1j","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons a type III demon in service to his patron that remains for [[/roll 1d4+1]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[24,26],"drawn":false},{"_id":"YUiXn4CrhzRe0PxZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons a type IV demon in service to his patron that remains for [[/roll 1d4+1]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[27,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hv7xMKjhk8YQwdZc","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons a type V demon in service to his patron that remains for [[/roll 1d4+1]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ziNjZbtIzO40PdXu","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons a type VI demon in service to his patron that remains for [[/roll 1d4+1]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"vp8si9he8Fx2i6Op","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster summons a type VI demon in service to his patron that remains for [[/roll 1d4+1]] turns.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":64,"range":[36,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"2Hlfwk9yyTZ9yvoT","name":"Force Manipulation","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.ayOZTpjSpOwIIC3d"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/glass-ball.svg","description":"<h1>Force Manipulation</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 25'</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 143</p><br><p>The caster conjures and shapes invisible force energy into useful objects or barriers of a solid nature. On a successful casting, the wizard may choose to invoke any effect of equal to or less than his spell check, allowing a range of options with every successful casting to produce a weaker but potentially more useful result.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Force Manipulation]{Force Manipulation}</p>","results":[{"_id":"3SyoFd0EY6lNRpyJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint + misfire; (1-2) corruption; (3) patron taint (or corruption if no patron); (4+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"g7Dkqzbd9KQ8zZSZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"AA9fENz4oLHpZQTT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster creates an apple-sized sphere of force that can be hurled as a weapon. It can be hurled immediately or remain in the wizards hand for up to one round per caster level. It inflicts [[/roll 1d6]] damage per caster level with a range of 25 per caster level.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"jACAig0ihWNimF0I","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard forms a floating platform of force energy 3 above the ground. This disk-shaped, 3 diameter platform follows him at a distance of 5 but can be commanded to move up to 25 away from the wizards position by thought alone. The platform can carry up to 100 lbs. per caster level and remains for [[/roll 1d6]]+CL turns. If circumstances prevent the disk from remaining within range of the caster, the platform vanishes.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"pUTVyhpfe7aAl9zW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster calls into being a tower shield-sized wall of force at a point within 25. It exists for [[/roll 2d6]] rounds and grants a +4 AC bonus to adjacent characters. The wall cannot move from where it was called into existence but remains in existence if the caster moves out of range.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"09Rt94EfVcRyKgjs","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"As above, but the spell creates two shield walls. Each also provides protection against magic missiles 50% of the time.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ox4wvFyGWURpaRR9","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster creates a wall of force 10 square per level in size. The wall cannot move but grants complete  protection against all physical attacks, magic missiles, heat, cold, and lightning. The wall takes the damage inflicted by such attacks. The wall lasts until [[/roll 1d6]]+CL turns have passed or it has absorbed 50 points of damage. The caster cannot attack or cast spells through the wall.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"iZ88T6UacT09BWuL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster creates a wall of force 10 square per level in size. He can form this wall into a spherical or hemispherical shape up to its maximum size in square feet. The wall cannot move, but grants complete protection against all physical attacks, magic missiles, heat, cold, and lightning. The wall takes the damage inflicted by such attacks. The wall lasts until [[/roll 1d6]]+CL hours have passed or it has absorbed 100 points of damage. The caster cannot attack or cast spells through the wall.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"B4skN1rzgcRFW2Ok","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster creates a wall of force 10 square per level in size. He can form this wall into any shape he can imagine, up to its maximum size in square feet. The wall cannot move, but grants complete protection against all physical attacks, all spells, and all dragon breath. The wall lasts until [[/roll 2d6]]+CL hours have passed or it has absorbed 150 points of damage. The caster cannot attack or cast spells through the wall.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"aVPgWp698g3HuUri","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster creates a wall of force 20 square per level in size. He can form this wall into any shape he can imagine, up to its maximum size in square feet. The wall can be moved up to 10 per round if the caster concentrates. It grants complete protection against all physical attacks, all spells, and all dragon breath. The wall lasts until [[/roll 2d6]]+CL days have passed or it has absorbed 300 points of damage. The caster may cast spell through the wall at opponents while enjoying its protection.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[32,32],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"2PbtdiJwhN52reJk","name":"Ekim's Mystical Mask","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.ZEDXMeUF2UBwsRCj"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/ceremonial-mask.svg","description":"<h1>Ekim's Mystical Mask</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round per CL</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> See below</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 137</p><br><p>The caster conjures a mystical mask that covers his face and provides benefits against attacks, spells, and other conditions. On a successful casting, the wizard may choose to invoke an effect of lesser power than his spell check roll to produce a weaker but potentially more useful result.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Ekim's Mystical Mask]{Ekim's Mystical Mask}</p>","results":[{"_id":"lZFxH45ZvsBvEZtA","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint + misfire; (1-2) corruption; (3+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"66v2B2c6bydgBRo4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"O6plosTMXv31tuvk","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The mask grants infravision, allowing the caster to see in the dark up to 60 away. His eyes reflect light like a cat while this mask is in effect.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"oD6fIkaNxXSb3ycx","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The mask helps protect the caster against gaze attacks such as that from a basilisk (q.v.). The caster enjoys a +4 bonus to saving throws of any type against gaze attacks for the duration of the spell. The casters face takes on a mirror-like quality while this mask is in effect.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hc4oOS9ZFAVEyVjr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The mask helps defend the caster against baneful magical spells. All spells cast directly at the wizard suffer a -2 penalty to their spell checks. Area-of-effect spells or other magics that are not targeted directly at the mask wearer are unmodified. The casters face takes on a faceted, quartz-like appearance while this mask is in effect.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fvrx0BUwvMwEvqR6","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The mask transforms the casters face into a horrible visage. Each round he can attempt to instill fear in one creature. The target creature must make a Will save or flee from the casters location for [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds. The targeted creature must be able to see the caster clearly to be affected by the gaze. <br /><br />The caster can attempt to affect one creature each round for the duration of the spell and can try to instill fear on the same creature more than once, requiring it to make a new saving throw with each attempt. The casters face becomes monstrously demonic while this mask is in effect.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wsXBvUkFsgT4iKhP","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The mask protects the caster against physical attacks, granting him a +4 bonus to AC while the spell is in effect. In addition, the caster enjoys a +2 bonus to all saving throws for the duration of the spell. The casters face appears encased in shining steel while this mask is in effect.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"U36Tlmd8LtisT9m3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The mask reflects melee and ranged attacks back at unlucky assailants. Any attacker that successfully strikes the masks wearer with a physical melee or missile attack must make a Luck check or find their attack turned against them. <br /><br />The attackers same attack roll (including any and all modifiers) is applied to its own AC and inflicts normal damage if the blow lands successfully. The casters face appears to be that of his attacker(s) while the mask is in effect.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"NzYVbi2Wo70zSq3j","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The mask transforms the casters entire head into that of a snake. While in effect, the mask grants the caster both the illusion generating and hypnotic gaze powers of a serpent-man (see page 425). As an incidental benefit, it also allows the caster to pass himself off as a serpent-man under cursory inspection. The masks effect on the casters face is self-evident.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fEW7F9HtTEU7P25k","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"With this powerful casting, the wizards face is occluded by a mask that combines all the spells possible effects into a single visage. The caster has infravision up to 60; gains a +4 saving throw bonus against gaze attacks; harmful spells cast directly at the caster suffer a -2 penalty to spell checks; the caster can instill fear against any creature that fails a Will save, forcing it to flee for [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds; the casters AC is improved by +4, and all saves receive a +2 bonus (this stacks with the +4 bonus against gaze attacks); any attacker who successfully strikes the caster with a physical melee or missile attack must make a Luck check or possibly be struck by its own attack (compare the initial attack roll against its own AC); and the casters face is transformed into a serpents head, granting him the illusionary and hypnotic capabilities of a serpent-man (see page 425). <br /><br />At this level of success, the mask makes no alterations to the casters face other than the snakes head transformation (which can be obscured with the illusion generation ability granted by that alteration).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"4DoCH0oWBDqfpyaO","name":"Ventriloquism","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.FTVcjrWS3bQMgmGN"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/puppet.svg","description":"<h1>Ventriloquism</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 30' or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round or more</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Sometimes (Will; see below)</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 158</p><br><p>The caster projects the sound of his voice from another place, such as an adjacent room, an animal or statue, down a hallway, etc.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Ventriloquism]{Ventriloquism}</p>","results":[{"_id":"AXh9xKcvwvzbZRZ8","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + misfire; (1-2) corruption; (3+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"pr1mamyvWdQpM4zA","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ugMJXUN9XSBUnJqu","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster projects one short phrase in his own voice to a place within 30' and line of sight. The position of origin is subject to the visual manifestation described above. Listeners that fail a Will save (rolled by judge) believe the noise to originate from the place designated; if they succeed on the save, they hear the voice from its true origin point of the caster's location.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8spyknUiZvvgEexM","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster projects a short phrase to a place within 30' and line of sight. He can use his own voice, or he can simulate another voice or sound that he has previously heard. For example, the caster can make the goblin captain appear to shout \"Retreat!\" in the goblin's own voice. The position of origin is subject to the visual manifestation described above. <br /><br />Listeners that fail a Will save (rolled by judge) believe the noise to originate from the place designated; if they succeed on the save, they hear the voice from its true origin point of the caster's location.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"b47ebOAlMuGm3ikP","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster projects a short phrase to a place within 30' and line of sight. He can use his own voice, or he can simulate another voice or sound that he has previously heard. For example, the caster can make the goblin captain appear to shout \"Retreat!\" in the goblin's own voice. There is no visual manifestation, only the sound created. <br /><br />Listeners that fail a Will save (rolled by judge) believe the noise to originate from the place designated; if they succeed on the save, they hear the voice from its true origin point of the caster's location.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rbwM1lkvZfMNAibM","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster projects a short phrase to a place within 30' and line of sight. He can use his own voice, or he can simulate another voice or sound that he has previously heard. For example, the caster can make the goblin captain appear to shout \"Retreat!\" in the goblin's own voice. There is no visual manifestation, and listeners receive no save; they automatically hear the noise from the point designated.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ahNeNbj2lgPUQIoe","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster projects sounds to a place within 60', even if it is beyond his line of sight. He can issue ongoing sounds for up to 1 turn as long as he concentrates. The caster can use his own voice, or he can simulate other voices or sounds he has previously heard. For example, he can simulate different voices in an ongoing conversation. There is no visual manifestation, and listeners receive no save; they automatically hear the noise from the point designated.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wsBoyy59BtpTCw3w","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster projects sounds to a range of up to 300', even beyond his line of sight For every full turn the caster concentrates, he can create an ongoing effect that lasts 1 hour, for a maximum duration of 24 hours. For example, he could concentrate for 3 turns and then leave an ongoing sound effect that lasts for 3 hours. Once the caster stops concentrating, the ongoing effect is \"prerecorded\"; i.e., the ongoing spell simulates the sounds requested (running water, stamping hooves, ongoing conversation, crackling fire, etc.), but the caster cannot change those sounds. <br /><br />The sounds created can be any the caster imagines, though ensuring accuracy requires him to have some reference point or have heard the sound before. Listeners do not receive a save.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"cUcOaK6FHdyg0YuE","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster projects sounds to a range of up to 1 mile, even beyond his line of sight. In addition, he can hear what is happening at the point where he throws his voice. For every full turn the caster concentrates, he can create an ongoing sound effect that lasts 1 day, for a maximum duration of 30 days. <br /><br />For example, he could concentrate for 3 turns and then leave an ongoing sound effect that lasts for 3 days (running water, stamping hooves, ongoing conversation, crackling fire, etc.). Once the caster stops concentrating, the ongoing effect continues, and he need only concentrate for one round to hear what is happening at the point of origin or change the running soundtrack should he so choose. The sounds created can be any the caster imagines, though ensuring accuracy requires him to have some reference point or have heard the sound before. Listeners do not receive a save.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"jMpGUGxHcOomcq1X","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can create nearly unlimited sound effects at will. He can create the sounds of massive thunderstorms, the crashing of waves on a cliff, the charge of a regiment of mounted knights, or the shouts of a thousand orcs. The sounds are true three-dimensional sounds; i.e., they surround the listeners and come from the appropriate directions not simply from a single origin point. <br /><br />The caster can extend these sound effects to a convincing range of 1 mile from the spell's target location, and that location can be anywhere that the caster has either personally visited (including other planes and dimensions) or currently has visibility to, even if that visibility is through scrying or a crystal ball. The caster can also hear all sounds from the target point as if he was standing there. <br /><br />Once he has cast the spell, the sound effect continues without concentration for up to 1 year or until the caster bids them cease. At any point, the caster can concentrate for one round to change the ongoing sound effect or hear what goes on at that place.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"4H4WJiv3rK4aqp76","name":"Demon Summoning","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.QnOXijbZVNU9PbIy"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/daemon-skull.svg","description":"<h1>Demon Summoning</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 20'</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 turn</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 206</p><br><p>Counts as with @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-wizard-3.Demon Summoning - Patron]{Demon Summoning - Patron}, @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-wizard-3.Demon Summoning - No Patron]{Demon Summoning - No Patron}, and @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-wizard-3.Demon Summoning - True Name]{Demon Summoning - True Name} depending on circumstances.</p>\n<p>The caster consults with an extraplanar spirit in order to make inquiries or pass on information. The spirit may be the ghost of a deceased person, a demon residing on another plane, a nature spirit occupying a lake or tree, the caster&rsquo;s own supernatural patron, or even a god.</p>\n<p>This spell is most effective if the caster consults with a spirit he already knows. If the caster consults with his patron (per the patron bond spell) or one of the patron&rsquo;s servants, add +1 to the spell check. If the caster consults with another specific spirit known to him from prior contact, legend, logical deduction (e.g., the</p>\n<p>caster sees a dead body and wishes to find its ghost), or research (e.g., the caster has visited his altar or read of his exploits), there is no modifier. If the caster has no knowledge of the spirit consulted, merely wishes to contact any spirit that will answer, or deliberately contacts a spirit of opposed alignment or interests, subtract -1 from the spell check.</p>\n<p>If the spirit is known to the caster, roll d% to determine its attitude: (01-20) friendly, (21-80) neutral, (81-00) hostile. A friendly or neutral spirit answers honestly to the best of its ability and has a base 50% chance of knowing the answer to any given question appropriate to its area of knowledge, modified by the judge&rsquo;s discretion and the obscurity of the question. When questioning a hostile spirit, roll d%: it (01-50) provides misleading information; (51-80) refuses to answer; (81-95) attempts to probe the caster&rsquo;s</p>\n<p>mind (Will save vs. DC of [[/roll 4d6]] or take [[/roll 1d4]] temporary Int damage); or (96-100) uses this connection to attempt enter the material plane.</p>\n<p>Note that establishing contact in this manner also enables the spirit to establish reverse contact on future</p>\n<p>occasions (by casting this same spell, if it is able, or other similar abilities). Furthermore, not all spirits are pleased at an interruption from a curious mortal. The ghost of a recently slain creature, for example, is probably quite angry at its death, and there may be consequences for awakening it.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Demon Summoning]{Demon Summoning}</p>","results":[{"_id":"ABVQX877a85URq4H","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Placeholder spell, Cast one of @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-wizard-3.Demon Summoning - Patron]{Demon Summoning - Patron}, @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-wizard-3.Demon Summoning - No Patron]{Demon Summoning - No Patron}, or @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spells-wizard-3.Demon Summoning - True Name]{Demon Summoning - True Name} depending on circumstances.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-100,100],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"4y4W5KhWYqobx948","name":"Feather Fall","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendiums.dcc-spell-tables.2evuVWdXpSirdV46"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/feather.svg","description":"<h1>Feather Fall</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 25'</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round per caster level or until landing</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> instantaneous</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will to avoid</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 140</p><br><p>The caster impedes his own or another person&rsquo;s rate of descent when falling. This allows the target to avoid injury or death or to glide upon the breeze. Note that this spell can be cast instantaneously, out of initiative order, if the caster or a target within range is falling.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Feather Fall]{Feather Fall}</p>","results":[{"_id":"viVWQ6mcJ20HZhss","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint + misfire; (1) corruption; (2) patron taint (or corruption if no patron); (3+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"moXeU4vC3UlMaBoX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"gUgyNfUqB4MbgzgG","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Caster reduces the speed at which he falls. With a successful Fortitude save (DC 10 +1 for each 10' fallen), he takes no damage. On a failed save, he suffers only half damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"IkPibmJi7c6pP6YW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Caster falls at a graceful rate of 50' per round and takes no damage if he lands before the spell expires. Otherwise, he suffers half damage and is allowed a Fort save (DC 10 +1 for each 20' fallen) to avoid all damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"S4DI7I9jBgPqsRrR","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Caster and three additional creatures within range fall at a rate of 50' round. They take no damage if they land before the spell expires. Otherwise, they suffer half damage and are allowed a Fort save (DC 10 +1 for each 20' fallen) to avoid all damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"RWJaiSn80PER9Jwb","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Caster and six additional creatures fall at a rate of 50' round. They take no damage if they land before the spell expires. Otherwise they suffer half damage and are allowed a Fort save (DC 10 +1 for each 20' fallen) to avoid all damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"np1yzPpQs9bJ5UTC","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Caster gains the ability to glide on the air by leaping from a height 30' or more above the ground. The caster soars on the breeze, drifting back to earth at a vertical rate of 10' per round, arriving on the ground when he reaches the maximum distance he can glide. His movement rate is 60' per round while gliding, and if he fails to reach solid ground before the spell expires, he falls and suffers normal damage upon impact.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"vfrUcNmIGfV49FYo","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Caster and up to three additional creatures can glide on the winds. They soar on the breeze, drifting back to earth at a vertical rate of 10' per round, arriving on the ground when reaching the maximum distance they can glide. Their movement rate is 60' per round while gliding, and if they fail to reach solid ground before the spell expires, they fall and suffer normal damage upon impact.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"",