{"_id":"5Qw1SGJXd0CRyv6E","name":"Enlarge","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendiums.dcc-spell-tables.E9f0suP2o46RtkKL"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/growth.svg","description":"<h1>Enlarge</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Touch</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 turn per caster level</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 139</p><br><p>By touching a creature or object, or targeting himself, the caster causes the target to grow in size! In this manner, ropes can become longer, doors thicker, tables heavier, swords larger, and so on. Magical objects so increased retain their original magical potency; e.g., a +1 sword does not become a +2 sword, it simply becomes a larger magical sword. The caster can learn the reverse of this spell, reduce, which is used to make things smaller. Multiple castings of this spell do not stack, though reduce may be used to cancel enlarge.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Enlarge]{Enlarge}</p>","results":[{"_id":"6qi6xp1VQ54PzqQw","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint + misfire; (1-2) corruption; (3) patron taint (or corruption if no patron); (4+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"i00Gu0bWAeh5mAPJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"0NWpx1inwbeaJTXa","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The target increases in size and mass by 10%. It becomes visibly larger and potentially intimidating, but not enough to confer statistical bonuses. Depending on the situation, this may be enough to reach a ledge that was previously out of reach, or otherwise pass so