{"_id":"EAiB3CSvH4jZA3Jz","name":"Detect Invisible","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.ygOHwJyiyfigK4Nz"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/secret-door.svg","description":"<h1>Detect Invisible</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 60' or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 Action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check DC</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 165</p><br><p>The caster activates an inner sight to see the true nature of things. In doing so, he is able to see invisible creatures and objects. If the target creature or object is protected by an invisibility shield (per the invisibility spell), the caster&rsquo;s spell check counts as the DC for the target&rsquo;s Will save.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Detect Invisible]{Detect Invisible}</p>","results":[{"_id":"ZV9QeVhwjZdbRNsY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint + misfire; (1-2) corruption; (3) patron taint; (4+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"punp2K81ZDUxJjx0","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"V63U1cMA2tRWiv6E","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"K064tMQqWeJ5pZGY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For a brief moment, the caster can see all invisible inanimate objects within 60'. Unless protected by a powerful invisibility shield (per the invisibility spell), these objects flicker into sight then immediately disappear again, leaving the caster with an impression of their location. The caster cannot see invisible creatures.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5n3ngTGJOZF7XrdU","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Until the end of the next round, the caster can see all invisible objects and creatures within 60'.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[16,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"IfhLxJULZdPAZ3pL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For the next turn, the caster can see all invisible objects and creatures within 60'.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[20,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"6PFGJZMepYWzGEVe","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For the next turn, the caster can see all invisible objects and creatures within 60'.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[22,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"BbddXykbrZ6RymbD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For the next turn, the caster can see all invisible objects and creatures within 200'. Additionally, one ally touched is also able to see invisible things as the caster, as long as he maintains physical contact with the ally. The ally can change round-to-round if the caster touches a different person.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[26,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Rq20sYIVIQflfbjx","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For the next hour, the caster and all allies within 10' can see all invisible objects and creatures within 200'.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"z6NZscKafcIJtLu9","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For the next hour, the caster and all allies within 10' can see all invisible objects and creatures within 200'. Additionally, the caster can dispel invisibility. If the caster concentrates for one round on an invisible object or creature, it must make a Will save against his spell check DC. <br /><br />If the Will save fails, the target's invisibility is temporarily suppressed. The power is lost for one round per missed point of the check. For example, if the DC was 32 and the creature's Will save was 24, it would be visible for 8 rounds. This ap-plies to creatures with native invisibility as well as spellcasters.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"0Dqwau4NESU1caEV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"With a powerful burst of radiant light, the caster suppresses the invisible nature of all invisible creatures and things within his line of sight. All objects, and creatures of 3 or less HD, are automatically made vis-ible for a period of one hour. Additionally, they must make a Will save or become permanently visible. <br /><br />Creatures of 4+ HD receive a Will save to resist the spell; failure means they also become visible for one hour. Visible creatures can be seen by all creatures. Note this effect includes friendly creatures who are invisible, as well as enemies. Finally, the caster (and only the caster) can see all secret doors, concealed compartments, hidden latches, and other such things. This ability lasts for the next hour.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":66,"range":[34,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
