{"_id":"PUj0p2o53GDQBmEt","name":"Make Potion","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.TKsIple5xpOFgfWd"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/cauldron.svg","description":"<h1>Make Potion</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Permanent</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> [[/roll 1d6+1]] hours + harvest/brewing (min 1 wk)</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 223</p><br><p>The caster creates mystical brews that grant supernormal powers to those who consume them. The result of the spell check determines which kind of potion can be created, as indicated below; each casting allows the caster to choose one potion from the eligible results at his spell check or less. This portion of the spell requires [[/roll 1d6+1]] hours to cast. Once a potion is decided upon, the caster must spend money equal to half the potion&rsquo;s spell check number (rounded down) &times; 25 gp to procure the necessary equipment and base ingredients for the potion. In addition, each brew requires a special substance that must be harvested by the caster himself and then brewed, which takes roughly one week after the spell is cast. See below for suggested special ingredients and more details on potion effects. Unlike other spells, the judge, not the caster, makes the spell check roll to determine the caster&rsquo;s success.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Make Potion]{Make Potion}</p>","results":[{"_id":"vYauI4nZJAcWFq2n","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse: Misfire and corruption!","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"eDXxXGxS5pcJT0iL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rAqT1oW1fGMWru