{"_id":"inC9ZETs9KjcGwef","name":"Paralysis (Wizard Casting)","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.WIvFzLMWvJjCb1Di"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/pause-button.svg","description":"<h1>Paralysis (Wizard Casting)</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Touch or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round or more</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will save vs. spell check</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 264</p><br><p>The light of the cleric&rsquo;s deity prevents his enemies from raising a hand to perform baleful deeds.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;This is the Wizard version of a Cleric spell as described in the footnote in @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.LxWvwON9h9JWpI6c]{Table 5-8: Wizard Spells}. The difficulty has been adjusted accordingly and a misfire added on a result of 1.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Paralysis (Wizard Casting)]{Paralysis (Wizard Casting)}</p>","results":[{"_id":"tdt9OdRhBwe2xqf4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"On a result of natural 1, the wizard suffers a 50% chance of major corruption or misfire, rolling on the generic tables as appropriate.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"JdfJT9AxYIiNJvfv","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":11,"range":[2,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"DW6Z7vsYmBsG5wHn","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The clerics hands and melee weapons are charged with the energy of paralysis. The cleric must make a normal attack on his next round. If it succeeds, he causes normal damage and his enemy must make a Will save or be paralyzed. The paralyzed creature is unable to move or take any physical action for [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,18],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5cPT21JPy3Kn0UP8","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The clerics hands and melee weapons are charged with the energy of paralysis. The charge remains for [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds. Any attack by the cleric during this period delivers normal damage plus paralysis if the target fails a Will save. The paralyzed creature is unable to move or take any physical action for [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[19,22],"drawn":false},{"_id":"7JazHBiiMqWIstbA","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The clerics melee weapons and missile fire weapons are charged with paralysis. The charge remains for [[/roll 1d4]]+CL rounds. Any attack by the cleric during this period delivers normal damage plus paralysis if the target fails a Will save. The paralyzed creature is unable to move or take any physical action for [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[23,24],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Cg0owmucw7YRIneW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric designates one creature within 30 and paralyzes it with a word. If the creature is 2 HD or less, it is automatically paralyzed. If 3 HD or more, it receives a Will save to resist. Paralysis lasts for  [[/roll 1d8]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[25,28],"drawn":false},{"_id":"glVyhvQWxpJkws7Z","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric designates up to three targets within 100 and paralyzes all of them. Any creature of 4 HD or less is automatically paralyzed. Creatures of 5 HD or more receive a Will save. Paralysis lasts for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[29,32],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Lp8JB9q3iyADpxkL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric imbues his touch with the power to paralyze an enemy. The cleric retains the latent paralysis touch for up to 24 hours. At any point during that time, he may discharge the paralysis with a spoken word. <br /><br />A melee attack may be necessary to touch a resisting target. The creature touched is automatically paralyzed if 6 HD or less. Creatures of 7+ HD receive a Will save. The paralysis lasts [[/roll 4d6]]+CL hours.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[33,34],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qkflWuy33SZzuE76","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Choose any one of the effects above, and the duration of the paralysis is doubled.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[35,36],"drawn":false},{"_id":"R50CRhik1SEBJwwi","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Choose any one of the effects above, and the duration of the paralysis is permanent. The paralysis can only be cured via magical means, such as a clerics ability to lay on hands or the spell cure paralysis.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[37,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"izXHihJOVwL4Q5aH","name":"Shatter","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.GGebq4xBbNcxGH3W"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/shattered-sword.svg","description":"<h1>Shatter</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Touch or further</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Instantaneous or longer</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> N/A</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 193</p><br><p>The caster shatters a physical object. This spell causes damage to inanimate objects and is particularly effective at objects made of crystal or glass. It has the potential to not only damage the object immediately but also cause ongoing fractures that make it more susceptible to future damage.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Shatter]{Shatter}</p>","results":[{"_id":"mTZJ9HS3Q5TJeSwv","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint + misfire; (1) corruption; (2) patron taint (or corruption if no patron); (3+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"jCDGGJO4LYsR85oY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"TyRkyET0Vpe8uYg3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"jGaX74EMzEVtWI7d","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"By touching a mundane (non-magical) inanimate object made of wood, metal, crystal, glass, stone, or another similar substance, the caster creates a fracture at the point of contact. This automatically inflicts [[/roll 1d4]] points of damage to the object, bypassing any normal resistance to damage. <br /><br />Typically, a dagger has 1-4 hit points, a sword has 4-6 hit points, and larger objects have progressively more hit points, depending on their construction (glass is weakest, wood is stronger, stone is even stronger, metal is strongest). This effect is typically enough to break a doorknob or hinge, shatter a glass window, snap a dagger blade from its hilt, or crack a mirror, but not enough to burst down a door. <br /><br />Using this spell in combat is dangerous, as the caster is exposed to attack when he attempts to touch the target object; opponents receive a free strike if the caster tries to touch them with this spell, and the caster must also succeed in an attack roll to make contact.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"JvMP5yRSpbmkgpro","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"By touching a mundane (non-magical) inanimate object made of wood, metal, crystal, glass, stone, or another similar substance, the caster creates a fracture at the point of contact. This automatically inflicts [[/roll 3d4]] points of damage to the object and an additional +2 points of damage if the object is glass or crystal or a gemstone, bypassing any normal resistance to damage. <br /><br />Typically, a dagger has 1-4 hit points, a sword has 4-6 hit points, and larger objects have progressively more hit points, depending on their construction (glass is weakest, wood is stronger, stone is even stronger, metal is strongest). This spell result is usually enough to shatter a sword, shield, or helm, break a wagon wheel, explode a mirror, or shatter a valuable gem (but not a diamond). <br /><br />Using this spell in combat is dangerous, as the caster is exposed to attack when he attempts to touch the target object; opponents receive a free strike if the caster tries to touch them with this spell, and the caster must also succeed in an attack roll to make contact.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[16,19],"drawn":false},{"_i