erous, as the caster is exposed to attack when he attempts to touch the target object; opponents receive a free strike if the caster tries to touch them with this spell, and the caster must also succeed in an attack roll to make contact.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[22,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MFw4ae042BAReTbV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"By touching an inanimate object made of wood, metal, crystal, glass, stone, or another similar substance, the caster creates a fracture at the point of contact. Alternatively, the caster can imbue the power of this spell on a single object (such as an arrow or dagger point). The spell is triggered when the object strikes something within the next round; after 1 round, the power dissipates. <br /><br />This allows the caster to enchant an arrow that can then be used to shatter an enemy's armor (for example). The spell automatically inflicts [[/roll 4d8]]+CL damage to mundane objects or [[/roll 2d6]] points of damage to magical objects (such as magic weapons). It inflicts an additional +4 points of damage if the object is glass or crystal or a gemstone, bypassing any normal resistance to damage. <br /><br />Typically, a dagger has 1-4 hit points, a sword has 4-6 hit points, and larger objects have progressively more hit points, depending on their construction (glass is weakest, wood is stronger, stone is even stronger, metal is strongest). Using this spell in combat is dangerous, as the caster is exposed to attack when he attempts to touch the target object; opponents receive a free strike if the caster tries to touch them with this spell, and the caster must also succeed in an attack roll to make contact.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[26,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"lCWsQuMXE4FZxh2G","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"By touching an inanimate object made of wood, metal, crystal, glass, stone, or another similar substance, the caster creates a fracture at the point of contact. Alternatively, the caster can imbue the power of this spell on a single object (such as an arrow or dagger point). The spell is triggered when the object strikes something within the next turn. <br /><br />This allows the caster to enchant an arrow that can then be used to shatter an enemy's armor (for example). The spell automatically inflicts  [[/roll 4d8]]+CL damage to mundane objects or [[/roll 2d6]] points of damage to magical objects (such as magic weapons). It inflicts an additional +4 points of damage if the object is glass or crystal or a gemstone, bypassing any normal resistance to damage. <br /><br />Typically, a dagger has 1-4 hit points, a sword has 4-6 hit points, and larger objects have progressively more hit points, depending on their construction (glass is weakest, wood is stronger, stone is even stronger, metal is strongest). Using this spell in combat is dangerous, as the caster is exposed to attack when he attempts to touch the target object; opponents receive a free strike if the caster tries to touch them with this spell, and the caster must also succeed in an attack roll to make contact.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"f7wiCaXaK12X99PQ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Within a range of 60', the caster can target an inanimate object made of wood, metal, crystal, glass, stone, or another similar substance, to create a fracture at the point of contact. Alternatively, the caster can imbue the power of this spell on a single object (such as an arrow or dagger point). The spell is triggered when that object strikes something within the next turn. <br /><br />This allows the caster to enchant an arrow that can then be used to shatter an enemy's armor (for example). The spell automatically inflicts [[/roll 4d8]]+CL damage to mundane objects or [[/roll 3d6]]+CL damage to magical objects (such as magic weapons). It inflicts an additional +4 points of damage if the object is glass or crystal or a gemstone, bypassing any normal resistance to damage. Typically, a dagger has 1-4 hit points, a sword has 4-6 hit points, and larger objects have progressively more hit points, depending on their construction (glass is weakest, wood is stronger, stone is even stronger, metal is strongest).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rLvLCRwX5x8IzWAx","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Within a range of 1,000', the caster can target an inanimate object made of wood, metal, crystal, glass, stone, or another similar substance, to create a fracture at the point of contact. At this level of casting, the caster can also target golems, automatons, living statues, and other animated but non-sentient creatures, which count as magical objects for purposes of the spell. <br /><br />Alternatively, the caster can imbue the power of this spell on a single object (such as an arrow or dagger point). The spell power remains on the object permanently, and the spell is triggered when that object strikes something. This allows the caster to enchant an arrow that can then be used to shatter an enemy's armor (for example). The spell automatically inflicts [[/roll 6d8]]+CL damage to mundane objects or [[/roll 4d6]]+CL damage to magical objects (such as magic weapons). <br /><br />It inflicts an additional +6 points of damage if the object is glass or crystal or a gemstone, bypassing any normal resistance to damage. Typically, a dagger has 1-4 hit points, a sword has 4-6 hit points, and larger objects have progressively more hit points, depending on their construction (glass is weakest, wood is stronger, stone is even stronger, metal is strongest).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":66,"range":[34,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"mwygsViHABQH2Kfk","name":"Binding (Wizard Casting)","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.9NsHtBRLNhAkAoYA"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/crossed-chains.svg","description":"<h1>Binding (Wizard Casting)</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 30 or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check DC</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 270</p><br><p>With this spell, the cleric binds a supernatural creature and forces it to obey his will. The spell is easiest if the creature has already been summoned for control via another spell. But the cleric may also cast this spell to control creatures encountered on their native planes.</p>\n<p>The cleric may target one creature already under the control of another spellcaster and summoned via another spell (for example, animal summoning, monster summoning, or invisible companion) or native to a non-material plane (for example, demons, devils, elementals, spirits, ghosts, etc.). The cleric binds that creature to obey his will instead of the will of its current master. A Will save is allowed to resist, but the Will save is made by the other spellcaster not the target creature, which is already dominated. If the check is successful, control of the bound creature transfers to the cleric casting binding. The cleric retains control for a time, after which control reverts back to the original caster (by which time the original summoning or controlling spell may have ended). This spell does not affect familiars or other creatures that voluntarily obey a spellcaster, only those under forcible control.</p>\n<p>Under certain circumstances, as noted below, the cleric may affect other targets as well.</p>\n<p>A creature under the cleric&rsquo;s control can be commanded to take any action normally within its power, similar to the animal summoning spell. The creature must be capable of hearing the cleric&rsquo;s commands and will execute them to the best of its ability. Suicidal or inherently contradictory commands grant the target another Will save to resist.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;This is the Wizard version of a Cleric spell as described in the footnote in @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-journals.LxWvwON9h9JWpI6c]{Table 5-8: Wizard Spells}. The difficulty has been adjusted accordingly and a misfire added on a result of 1.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Binding (Wizard Casting)]{Binding (Wizard Casting)}</p>","results":[{"_id":"vADnCrVPI4zFxBx8","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"On a result of natural 1, the wizard suffers a 50% chance of major corruption or misfire, rolling on the generic tables as appropriate.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rnzNM6eTWaQIDMkX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":13,"range":[2,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"DME0bDWeBNf9tZQJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 2 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 1d6]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"pXK6v2QuZ5gdU4XD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 4 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[18,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"FF8oCz3cW7gFCM1H","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 6 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[22,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hGRvtqlZ6cwSsDjZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 6 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL rounds. Alternately, the cleric may also choose to target one free-willed extraplanar creature of 4 HD or less currently on a non-native plane. It receives a Will save using its own modifier. The cleric controls the creature as if it were under the effects of an animal summoning spell of the same spell check. At the end of the duration, the creature reverts to its own free will.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"CmrEY6w90q6zeDLU","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 8 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL turns. Alternately, the cleric may also choose to target one free-willed extraplanar creature of 6 HD or less currently on a non-native plane. It receives a Will save using its own modifier. The cleric controls the creature as if it were under the effects of an animal summoning spell of the same spell check. At the end of the duration, the creature reverts to its own free will.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[28,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"oGudBZOInx9FIYwo","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 8 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL turns. Alternately, the cleric may also choose to target one other creature of 8 HD or less, which can be any free-willed extraplanar creature currently on a non-native plane, any mundane animal, or any unintelligent monster. It receives a Will save using its own modifier. The cleric controls the creature as if it were under the effects of an animal summoning spell of the same spell check. At the end of the duration, the creature reverts to its own free will.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"uyIRnyFFuiomkbXE","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 12 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL hours. Alternately, the cleric may also choose any other target, whether intelligent or not,  or extraplanar or not, of up to 10 HD or less. It receives a Will save using its own modifier. The cleric controls the creature as if it were under the effects of an animal summoning spell of the same spell check. At the end of the duration, the creature reverts to its own free will.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"cFa3M3iAbJ8w0b7V","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target any creature of any Hit Dice or power level and attempt to control that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL days. At the end of the duration, the creature reverts to its own free will.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[36,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
