tic reader of the scroll receives a -2 penalty to the check).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wiBMf5B5QDk7jLNs","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster can transcribe up to eight spells of any level. Additionally, the caster can transcribe the scroll such that a reader other than himself or a designated subject may be subject to a curse or rune. The curse or rune must be generated via a separate spell, but that spell does not count toward the spells recorded on a scroll. <br /><br />The caster can also transcribe the spells in a manner such that the spell check is pre-determined. The caster must make a spell check for each spell he writes. When the scroll is read, the spells are cast at that spell check result automatically, with no need for an additional check by the reader.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":64,"range":[36,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
