{"_id":"sFskQxYrwiqk9tSs","name":"Mirror Image","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.d63hGoBBBpFbHr2J"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/mirror-mirror.svg","description":"<h1>Mirror Image</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self or touch</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round or longer</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check DC</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 182</p><br><p>This spell creates illusionary doubles of the caster, which mimic his actions exactly. They appear in the space directly around him and distract opponents, who tend to strike the mirror images instead of the caster. More powerful castings can create duplicates of allies or objects. The total number of doubles the caster can create of himself, allies, or objects cannot exceed his Int score.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Mirror Image]{Mirror Image}</p>","results":[{"_id":"NlhqWpRL50OQPTGK","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost, failure, and worse! Roll [[/roll 1d6]] modified by Luck: (0 or less) corruption + patron taint + misfire; (1-3) corruption; (4) patron taint (or corruption if no patron); (5+) misfire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"gkZQrXAcWrzvI2fa","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lost. Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":10,"range":[2,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"zw9NjWIscN6OjHhZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure, but spell is not lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"f5VXXh7KYtpT8Bye","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A single mirror image blinks into existence directly adjacent to the caster. It looks exactly like him, and mimics his actions and speech. It must remain within 5' of the caster at all times. An